## PHASE 1 — DISCOVERY & RESEARCH (Days 1–3)

### 1A. Market & Persona Research

- [ ] **P0** `1A.1` — **Compile gig worker income data across 5 target cities**
  - Owner: Research Lead
  - Depends: None
  - Sources: NITI Aayog gig economy report, ILO India, NSSO periodic surveys, Fairwork India 2025
  - Acceptance:
    - [ ] City-wise average daily earnings (Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore, Hyderabad, Chennai)
    - [ ] Earnings variance and seasonal fluctuation data
    - [ ] Platform-specific breakdown (Zepto, Blinkit, Swiggy Instamart)
    - [ ] Vulnerability index: % workers earning < ₹15,000/month
  - Est: 4h

- [ ] **P0** `1A.2` — **Map weather disruption frequency using IMD historical data**
  - Owner: Data Eng
  - Depends: None
  - Sources: IMD open data, OpenWeatherMap historical API, India WRIS
  - Acceptance:
    - [ ] 3-year monthly disruption event count per city (rain >50mm, heat >42°C, AQI >400, flood alerts)
    - [ ] Disruption heatmap visualization (city × month × event-type)
    - [ ] Monsoon vs non-monsoon disruption ratio
    - [ ] Average disruption duration per event type
  - Est: 6h

- [ ] **P0** `1A.3` — **Benchmark existing parametric insurance solutions**
  - Owner: Research Lead
  - Depends: None
  - Targets: Plutas.ai, SEWA heatwave program, MIC Global + WRMS flood cover, J-PAL Delhi NCR pilot
  - Acceptance:
    - [ ] Feature comparison matrix (triggers, payouts, pricing, onboarding, fraud detection)
    - [ ] Gap analysis: what none of them does that we will
    - [ ] Pricing benchmarks (premium ranges, coverage amounts, loss ratios)
  - Est: 3h

### 1B. Technical Feasibility

- [ ] **P0** `1B.1` — **Shield-SAC algorithm feasibility assessment**
  - Owner: ML Eng
  - Depends: None
  - Acceptance:
    - [ ] Reproduce basic SAC agent from PyTorch examples on simple env
    - [ ] Implement shield mechanism (action clipping) on toy pricing problem
    - [ ] Synthetic data generator: 1000 worker-weeks with weather features
    - [ ] Go/No-Go decision documented with rationale
    - [ ] If No-Go: XGBoost + fairness post-processing fallback spec written
  - Est: 8h

- [ ] **P0** `1B.2` — **Apply for Guidewire Cloud Platform sandbox access**
  - Owner: Backend Lead
  - Depends: None
  - Acceptance:
    - [ ] Application submitted to Guidewire partner portal
    - [ ] Sandbox access confirmed OR fallback plan documented (simulate GWCP APIs)
    - [ ] If access granted: PolicyCenter and ClaimCenter accessible
  - Est: 2h

- [ ] **P1** `1B.3` — **Evaluate WhatsApp Business API for onboarding bot**
  - Owner: Frontend Lead
  - Depends: None
  - Acceptance:
    - [ ] Meta Business API vs Twilio comparison (cost, template approval time, regional language support)
    - [ ] Message template requirements documented (WhatsApp has 24-hour response window rules)
    - [ ] Proof-of-concept: send/receive WhatsApp message via chosen API
  - Est: 3h

- [ ] **P1** `1B.4` — **Evaluate external APIs (weather, traffic, payments)**
  - Owner: Backend Eng
  - Depends: None
  - Acceptance:
    - [ ] OpenWeatherMap free tier: verify rate limits (60 calls/min), response latency, Indian city accuracy
    - [ ] Razorpay Instant Payout sandbox: verify UPI payout flow, test with ₹1 transaction
    - [ ] Google Maps Traffic API (or mock alternative): delay index availability for Indian cities
  - Est: 4h

### 1C. Parametric Model Definition

- [ ] **P0** `1C.1` — **Define 5 parametric trigger thresholds with statistical justification**
  - Owner: ML Eng + Research Lead
  - Depends: `1A.2`
  - Acceptance:
    - [ ] Each trigger has: type, threshold, data source, payout range, historical frequency
    - [ ] Thresholds calibrated against IMD data (not arbitrary numbers)
    - [ ] Expected trigger frequency per city per month documented
    - [ ] Actuarial loss ratio estimate per trigger type
  - Details:
    ```
    HEAVY_RAIN:  >50 mm/hr   | Source: OWM  | Payout: ₹200-400  | Freq: ~4/month (Mumbai monsoon)
    FLOOD:       zone active  | Source: CWC  | Payout: ₹400-800  | Freq: ~2/month (monsoon)
    HEATWAVE:    >42°C        | Source: IMD  | Payout: ₹200      | Freq: ~6/month (May-June Delhi)
    POLLUTION:   AQI >400     | Source: CPCB | Payout: ₹150      | Freq: ~8/month (Nov-Jan Delhi)
    CURFEW:      alert active | Source: ACLED| Payout: ₹300      | Freq: ~0.5/month
    ```
  - Est: 5h

- [ ] **P0** `1C.2` — **Design Disruption Severity Index (DSI) formula**
  - Owner: ML Eng
  - Depends: `1A.2`, `1C.1`
  - Acceptance:
    - [ ] Formula documented: DSI = 0.4×S_weather + 0.3×S_traffic + 0.3×S_orders
    - [ ] Each sub-score normalized to 0-100 with clear calculation steps
    - [ ] DSI thresholds defined (30/50/65/80/90) with action at each level
    - [ ] Validated against 10+ historical disruption events (back-tested)
  - Est: 4h

